race.comment: SHORTY BOY (7) is a promising type who notched his 13th career success when too good (25.10) at Ballarat last time. Solid winning record at this trip. Has a strong record out of this box with three wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. BABY GIRL PEARL (6) had been racing in honest fashion recording three placings in a row before finishing fourth (30.10) at Sandown latest. Form at the trip sound including three wins. Shapes as one to consider. PAW TABITHA (2) was never in contention last time after missing the jump at Warragul, but prior to that won by a neck at Ballarat (22.33) beating Croydon in a Grade 4/5 on October 22. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Likely to be thereabouts. OLLIE DEEDS (1) can fill a top-three spot.
